gomodel:SYNGO_2570  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Ghrelin is a peptide that acts on the GHS-R1a receptor in hippocampal neurons to induce synaptic potentiation.\n\nFig.5: \"Ghrelin receptor activation increases the cell-surface trafficking of GluA1-AMPAR mediated by cLTP.\"\n\nFig.7: \"Ghrelin receptor activation triggers changes in GluA1 and stargazin phosphorylation and the PKA and PKC signaling pathways are required for increased GluA1-AMPAR surface expression induced by ghrelin receptor activation in the hippocampus.\". Experimental description: \"Hippocampal slices (300 μm) were obtained from male Sprague-Dawley rats\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2570" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

